HER2 "stimulates the growth of various types of cancer," including breast, ovarian, lung and colorectal cancers, explained Prof Berzofsky.
A similar approach of taking immune cells from patients and how they are "taught" how to target cancer cells has worked in the treatment of a type of leukaemia.
